✅ 1️⃣ 50 C# Coding Problems (Easy → Hard)
I’ll group them so you know what interviewers are testing.
🟢 Easy (Basics & Logic)

Reverse a string
Check palindrome
Find largest / smallest number
Sum of digits
Fibonacci series
Factorial (iterative & recursive)
Count vowels/consonants
Swap two numbers without temp
Check prime number
Count occurrences in array


 Medium (LINQ, Collections, Algorithms)

Second highest number
Remove duplicates from list
Merge two sorted arrays
Find missing number (1–N)
First non‑repeating character
Group words by anagram
Flatten nested collections (SelectMany)
Intersection of two lists
LINQ join between two objects
Sort dictionary by value

🔵 Medium‑Hard (Real‑World)

Validate brackets ({[]})
Find longest substring without repeating chars
Binary search implementation
Convert List to Dictionary safely
Paginate list manually
Find top N elements efficiently
Cache results using Dictionary
Implement custom comparer
Count word frequencies from string
Implement stack using array

🔴 Hard (Senior Level / Architecture Thinking)

Thread‑safe singleton
Producer‑consumer using BlockingCollection
LRU Cache implementation
Deadlock example & fix
Rate limiter (in‑memory)
Retry mechanism with exponential backoff
Detect circular dependency
Async parallel execution with throttling
Memory‑efficient large file read
Implement pipeline using Delegates

⚫ Very Hard (System Thinking)

Custom middleware
Generic repository with Unit of Work
Distributed cache fallback logic
API idempotency logic
Optimistic concurrency handling
CQRS write vs read model
Event‑driven order processing
Bulk insert optimization
Circuit breaker logic
Design a background job system

